#      (extention)

a + d

# 2.9.2 , , , ,  
a * 2
a ^ 2
a / 2
a %% 2
a %/% 2

# 2.10  
a > 2
a >= 2
a < 2
a <= 2
a == 2
a != 2

# 2.11  
a >= 1
b <= 2
a >= 1 & b <= 2
a >= 1 | b <= 2
!(a >= 1 & b <= 2)

# 2.12   : %in%
x <- 0
x == a[1]
x == a[2]
x == a[3]
x == a[1] | x == a[2] | x == a[3]
x %in% a

# 4.2.1     : data.frame()
#       
num <- seq(from = 1, to = 10, by = 2)
chr <- rep(x = c('a', 'b'), each = 3)

#      <-   .
df1 <- data.frame(num, chr)

# cha  num   
cha <- letters[1:5]

#     
df1 <- data.frame(num, cha)

# df1 
print(x = df1)

# df1  
class(x = df1)


# 4.2.2     : str()
# df1  
str(object = df1)

#    
options('max.print')

# df1     
View(x = df1)

# stringsAsFactors  
options('stringsAsFactors')

# data.frame()  stringsAsFactors  
df2 <- data.frame(num, cha, stringsAsFactors = TRUE)

# df2  
str(object = df2)


# 4.3.1  
# df1 1, 1 
df1[1, 1]

# df1 1~2, 1~2 
df1[1:2, 1:2]

# df1 1 
df1[1, ]

# df1 1~2 
df1[1:2, ]

# df1 1 
df1[, 1]

# df1 1~2 
df1[, 1:2]

# df1  num  
df1[, 'num']

df1$num

#     
df1$num >= 5

#        
df1[df1$num >= 5, ]

# df1$num  5   cha  
df1[df1$num >= 5, 'cha']

# df1$num  5   cha

# 4.4.1    : $ 
# df1

# 4.4.2    : cbind()

# df1   
str(object = df1)
